ee360 multiuser wireless systems and networks winter 2012 ee360 multiuser wireless systems and networks winter 2012 professor andrea goldsmith this course will focus on fundamental principles as well as current research issues in multiple access techniques including mimo systems cellular systems ad hoc wireless networks cognitive radio systems wireless sensor networks and cross layer wireless network design lectures will be based on required reading from the textbook complemented by magazine and journal articles active class participation is mandatory required reading must be done before class and in class time will be divided between lectures and group discussions each student will be required to present a paper on one of the course topics to the class the course grade will be based on class participation several paper surveys based on the required and supplemental reading several homework assignments based on the required reading and a final project basic course information tentative syllabus announcements project guidelines guidelines for paper summaries lectures homeworks class projects class website in 2010 resources
